%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104545253%2F104545253.jpg%3F187396%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Ftamil%2Fmovie-reviews%2Fleo%2Fmovie-review%2F104545253.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104545253.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThough%20the%20whole%20%E2%80%98LCU%E2%80%99%20part%20looks%20forced%2C%20one%20can%20say%20that%20with%20Leo%2C%20Lokesh%20has%20a%20strongest%20shot%20in%20his%20arm%20for%20the%20next%20franchise.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sridevi%20S%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Ftamil%2Fmovie-reviews%2Fleo%2Fmovie-review%2F104545253.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reconsidering%20PMLA%20Judgment%3A%20SC%20Asserts%20its%20Power%20to%20Refer%20it%20to%20a%20Larger%20Bench%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F17134928%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_01-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20special%20bench%20comprising%20three%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%C2%A0%20Court%20on%20Wednesday%20(October%2018)%20appeared%20inclined%20to%20consider%20arguments%20in%20favour%20of%20referring%20the%20July%202022%20judgment%20of%20the%20court%20in%20%3Cem%3EVijay%20Madanlal%20Choudhary%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20a%20Constitution%20bench%20of%20five%20judges.%20The%20judgment%20upholding%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%2C%20delivered%20by%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20led%20by%20Justice%20A.M.%20Khanwilkar%20who%20had%20since%20retired%2C%20was%20highly%20controversial%20in%20view%20of%20its%20adverse%20effects%20on%20citizens%E2%80%99%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20already%20has%20review%20and%20curative%20jurisdictions%20to%20reconsider%20its%20judgments%20on%20specific%20grounds.%20But%20these%20jurisdictions%20have%20been%20found%20to%20be%20inadequate%20to%20consider%20challenges%20to%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgments%20on%20substantial%20grounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20review%20jurisdiction%20enables%20the%20court%20to%20correct%20errors%20apparent%20on%20the%20face%20of%20the%20record%2C%20while%20the%20curative%20jurisdiction%20enables%20a%20litigant%20to%20challenge%20a%20judgment%20of%20the%20apex%20court%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20violation%20of%20natural%20justice.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20generally%20discourages%20litigants%20from%20filing%20writ%20petitions%20to%20challenge%20judgments%20delivered%20by%20it%20earlier.%20The%20review%20and%20curative%20petitions%20are%20generally%20heard%20in%20chambers%20by%20judges%20who%20had%20given%20the%20verdict%20earlier%2C%20and%20if%20those%20judges%20had%20retired%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20successor%20judges%20are%20nominated%20to%20hear%20them%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20in%20his%20administrative%20capacity.%20Although%20most%20review%20and%20curative%20petitions%20get%20dismissed%20by%20the%20judges%2C%20some%20of%20them%20do%20get%20their%20approval%20for%20%E2%80%98open%20hearing%E2%80%99%2C%20when%20lengthy%20arguments%20are%20heard%20and%20decided.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20July%202022%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3EVijay%20Madanlal%20Choudhary%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20delivered%20by%20a%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20Khanwilkar%2C%20Dinesh%20Maheshwari%20and%20C.T.%20Ravikumar%20had%20upheld%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20the%20power%20of%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20to%20arrest%20in%20money%20laundering%20cases.%20It%20upheld%20various%20contested%20provisions%20of%20the%20PMLA%2C%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20all%20the%20provisions%20have%20a%20reasonable%20nexus%20with%20the%20objects%20sought%20to%20be%20achieved%20by%20the%20Act%20in%20preventing%C2%A0%20money-laundering%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2025%2C%202022%2C%20the%20court%20heard%20the%20review%20petitions%20in%20open%20court%20and%20observed%20that%20its%20judgment%20required%20reconsideration%20on%20two%20aspects%3A%20non-supply%20of%20the%20Enforcement%20Case%20Information%20Report%20(ECIR)%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20akin%20to%20the%20FIR%20in%20other%20cases%20%E2%80%93%20to%20the%20accused%3B%20and%20the%20reversal%20of%20the%20presumption%20of%20innocence%20of%20the%20accused%20under%20Section%2045(1)%20of%20the%20PMLA.%20The%20review%20was%20heard%20by%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20comprising%20the%20then%20CJI%2C%20N.V.%20Ramana%2C%20and%20Justices%20Maheshwari%20and%20Ravikumar%2C%20as%20Justice%20Khanwilkar%20had%20retired%20in%20July%202022.%20Chief%20Justice%20Ramana%20had%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20his%20brother%20judges%20on%20the%20bench%20were%20not%20agreeable%20to%20examine%20issues%20other%20than%20the%20two%20aspects.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20with%20the%20review%20petition%20still%20pending%20before%20the%20court%2C%20the%20case%20was%20listed%20along%20with%20other%20cases%20before%20another%20three-judge%20bench%2C%20comprising%20Justices%20S.K.%20Kaul%2C%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20Bela%20M.%20Trivedi.%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20vehemently%20protested%20against%20the%20hearing%20as%20in%20his%20view%2C%20it%20is%20tantamount%20to%20hearing%20an%20appeal%20over%20another%20coordinate%20bench%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20would%20constitute%20an%20abuse%20of%20process%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustices%20Kaul%2C%20Khanna%20and%20Trivedi%2C%20however%2C%20found%20nothing%20unusual%20in%20the%20hearing%20of%20the%20case%2C%20as%20in%20their%20view%20only%20if%20they%20found%20a%3Cem%3E%20prima%20facie%20%3C%2Fem%3Eground%20for%20reconsidering%20the%202022%20judgment%20would%20it%20be%20referred%20to%20a%20larger%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20submitted%20that%20this%20new%20practice%20by%20the%20court%20would%20enable%20any%20litigant%20unhappy%20with%20a%20decision%20of%20the%20court%20to%20approach%20another%20bench%20of%20the%20court%20to%20reconsider%20it%2C%20thus%20skipping%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20review%20jurisdiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kaul%20dismissed%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20apprehension%20that%20there%20is%20reason%20for%20the%20court%20to%20be%20alarmed%20by%20this%20new%20practice.%20Justice%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%20answer%20was%20that%20the%20court%20was%20%E2%80%9Calert%E2%80%9D%20to%20this%20departure%20from%20the%20standard%20practice%2C%20but%20certainly%20not%20%E2%80%9Calarmed%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20the%20court%20had%20sufficient%20powers%20to%20revisit%20its%20judgments%20to%20correct%20injustice.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20then%20sought%20to%20persuade%20the%20bench%20to%20defer%20its%20hearing%20by%20a%20month%2C%20in%20view%20of%20the%20periodic%20evaluation%20by%20the%20Financial%20Action%20Task%20Force%20(FATF)%2C%20a%20global%20money%20laundering%20and%20terrorist%20financing%20watchdog%20whose%20guidelines%20were%20a%20trigger%20to%20enact%20the%20PMLA.%20He%20invoked%20the%20ground%20of%20national%20interest%20to%20persuade%20the%20bench%20unsuccessfully.%20But%20the%20bench%20disagreed%2C%20saying%20that%20its%20hearing%20the%20case%20cannot%20be%20against%20the%20national%20interest.%20Frequent%20interruptions%20by%20Mehta%20and%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20S.V.%20Raju%20during%20the%20proceedings%20led%20to%20Justice%20Kaul%20reasserting%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20hear%20the%20matter.%20As%20Justice%20Kaul%20is%20retiring%20on%20December%2025%2C%20the%20government%20appeared%20to%20be%20keen%20on%20delaying%20the%20hearing%2C%20so%20that%20it%20could%20be%20listed%20before%20another%20bench%20which%20Justice%20Kaul%20may%20not%20be%20a%20part%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20will%20hear%20the%20matter%20again%20on%20November%2022%2C%20when%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20counsel%20are%20expected%20to%20articulate%20reasons%20why%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20review%20jurisdiction%20is%20insufficient%20to%20reconsider%20the%202022%20verdict%2C%20now%20under%20challenge%20on%20many%20constitutional%20grounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697694469000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F17134928%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_01-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Freconsidering-pmla-judgment-sc-asserts-its-power-to-refer-it-to-a-larger-bench%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20special%20bench%20has%20agreed%20to%20revisit%20its%202022%20judgment%20upholding%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%2C%20and%20refer%20it%20to%20a%20larger%20bench%20if%20necessary.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Freconsidering-pmla-judgment-sc-asserts-its-power-to-refer-it-to-a-larger-bench%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22YouTuber%20Gaurav%20Taneja%20Claims%20He%20Earns%20More%20Than%20AirAsia%20CEO%20Who%20Fired%20Him%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EGaurav%20Taneja%2C%20who%20is%20known%20for%20his%20YouTube%20channel%20%26quot%3BFlying%20Beast%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20finally%20answered%20the%20million-dollar%20question%20about%20his%20monthly%20earnings.%20In%20a%20recent%20interview%20conducted%20by%20Raj%20Shamani%2C%20Mr%20Taneja%20said%20that%20he%20earns%20more%20than%20the%20CEO%20of%20AirAsia%2C%20the%20company%20that%20had%20fired%20him%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FNr75yJ_nXnQ%3Fsi%3DcaXDlE1Jr9oOBl49%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cst