4%2F11232732%2F183895317_2ead418efa_k.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20According%20to%20the%20latest%20World%20Bank%20data%2C%20extreme%20poverty%20in%20India%20declined%20in%202021%20%E2%80%93%20after%20a%20surge%20in%202019%20and%202020%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20but%20remained%20above%20the%202018%20level.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20pandemic%20resulted%20in%20an%20increase%20in%20poverty%20for%20most%20countries%20around%20the%20world%2C%20poverty%20in%20India%20was%20already%20showing%20an%20upward%20trend%20in%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202018%2C%20151.79%20million%20Indians%20were%20categorised%20under%20this%20head%20which%20shot%20up%20to%C2%A0%20176.09%20million%20in%202019%20%E2%80%93%20an%20increase%20of%20nearly%2024%20million.%20India%E2%80%99s%20poverty%20rate%20at%2011.9%25%20in%202021%20also%20remained%20higher%20than%20the%202018%20level%20of%2011.09%25%2C%20though%20easing%20from%2014.72%25%20in%202020%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusinessline%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fextreme-poverty-in-india-eased-in-2021-but-remained-above-2018-level-123101801314_1.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20World%20Bank%20measures%2C%20the%20extreme%20poverty%20rate%20is%20set%20at%20%242.15%20a%20day%20(approximately%20Rs%20180)%20in%20purchasing%20power%20parity%20terms.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20global%20lender%20used%20data%20from%20the%20Consumer%20Pyramids%20Household%20Survey%2C%20conducted%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy%2C%20to%20estimate%20poverty%20for%20India%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20Household%20Consumer%20Expenditure%20Survey%20(CES)%20data%20from%20the%20government%20since%202011-12%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusinessline%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fextreme-poverty-in-india-eased-in-2021-but-remained-above-2018-level-123101801314_1.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20results%20for%202022-23%20and%202023-24%20CES%20are%20likely%20to%20come%20only%20after%20the%202024%20general%20elections%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fresults-of-consumer-expenditure-surveys-2022-23-2023-24-only-after-2024-elections-report%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20had%20reported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20findings%20of%20a%20similar%20exercise%20done%20by%20the%20government%20in%202017-2018%20were%20withheld%20but%20the%20leaked%20data%20had%20shown%20a%20rise%20in%20poverty%20levels%20and%20a%2045-year%20high%20in%20unemployment%20in%202018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-poverty-estimates-shot-in-dark%5C%22%3ERecent%20Poverty%20Estimates%20Are%20Little%20More%20Than%20a%20Shot%20in%20the%20Dark%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFormer%20member%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20Planning%20Commission%20N.C.%20Saxena%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fextreme-poverty-in-india-eased-in-2021-but-remained-above-2018-level-123101801314_1.html%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20there%20were%20many%20reasons%20why%20poverty%20might%20have%20increased%20before%20the%20pandemic%20in%202018-19.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%202017-18%20consumption%20survey%20that%20it%20junked%20had%20shown%20that%20poverty%20increased%20in%20India.%20In%20the%202005-2015%20period%2C%20there%20was%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20investment%20in%20construction%2C%20which%20declined%20after%202015.%20So%2C%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people%20who%20were%20involved%20in%20construction%20activity%20lost%20their%20jobs.%20The%20latest%20figures%20also%20show%20there%20has%20been%20no%20increase%20in%20real%20wages.%20The%20number%20of%20people%20who%20are%20in%20the%20workforce%20has%20also%20not%20increased%20significantly.%20Therefore%2C%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people%20are%20in%20the%20third%20category%20of%20%E2%80%98neither%20employed%20nor%20seeking%20employment%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fextreme-poverty-in-india-eased-in-2021-but-remained-above-2018-level-123101801314_1.html%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EBusinessline%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20World%20Bank%20also%20made%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fextreme-poverty-in-india-eased-in-2021-but-remained-above-2018-level-123101801314_1.html%5C%22%3Esignificant%20upward%20revision%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20its%20previous%20estimate%20of%20the%20number%20of%20people%20living%20in%20extreme%20poverty%20in%202019.%20The%20new%20estimate%20is%20176.09%20million%2C%20whereas%20the%20earlier%20estimate%20was%20136.81%20million.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20narrowed%20the%20gap%20with%20the%202020%20figures%20to%2029.5%20million%2C%20implying%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fextreme-poverty-in-india-eased-in-2021-but-remained-above-2018-level-123101801314_1.html%5C%22%3Epandemic%20had%20a%20smaller%20debilitating%20impact%20on%20poverty%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20previously%20thought.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20World%20Bank%20had%20said%20about%2056%20million%20Indians%20may%20have%20plunged%20into%20extreme%20poverty%20in%202020%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20increasing%20the%20global%20tally%20by%2071%20million%20and%20making%20it%20the%20worst%20year%20for%20poverty%20reduction%20since%20World%20War%20II%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusinessline%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697693102000