0to%20perform%20the%20dance%20publicly%20to%20reduce%20the%20taboo%20around%20it.%20She%20went%20on%20to%20become%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20celebrated%20dancers%20and%20the%20first%20revivalist%20of%20Indian%20classical%20forms.%20In%201956%2C%20she%20was%20awarded%20the%20Padma%20Bhushan%20and%20in%201967%2C%20she%20received%20the%20Sangeet%20Natak%20Akademi%20Award.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697467160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D332286%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rukmini%20Devi%20Arundale%20wanted%20to%20transform%20the%20way%20people%20looked%20at%20Bharatnatyam%2C%20a%20dance%20form%20which%20was%20once%20performed%20only%20by%20devadasis.%20She%20and%20her%20husband%20established%20a%20dance%20and%20music%20academy%20called%20Kalakshetra%20at%20Adyar%20near%20Chennai%20to%20encourage%20others%20to%20learn%20such%20art%20forms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Tina%20Freese%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F332286%2Frukmini-devi-arundale-legendary-bharatnatyam-dancer-kalakshetra-founder-adyar-chennai-president%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20A%20Bengaluru%20Chef%20is%20Upcycling%20Leftover%20Grains%20From%20Breweries%20Into%20Flour%2C%20Brownies%2C%20Laddus%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBengaluru%2C%20with%20over%2060%20microbreweries%2C%20is%20recognised%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20beer%20hub%2C%20attracting%20numerous%20corporate%20workers%20every%20weekend%20to%20savour%20its%20newly%20crafted%20beers.%20Yet%2C%20it%20produces%20approximately%2012%2C000%20kilograms%20of%20wheat%20and%20barley%20byproducts%20daily%2C%20often%20repurposed%20as%20cattle%20feed%20or%20accumulating%20in%20landfills%20alongside%20other%20food%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFood%20waste%20produces%20methane%2C%20and%20it%20is%20estimated%20that%20methane%20is%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fgmi%2Fimportance-methane%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E25%20times%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20harmful%20as%20carbon%20dioxide%20in%20trapping%20heat%20in%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBengaluru%E2%80%99s%20Elizabeth%20Yorke%20is%20upcycling%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F260581%2Fodisha-beer-byproduct-plastic-alternative-edible-cutlery-innovation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espent%20grain%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20a%20byproduct%20in%20the%20beer%20brewing%20process%20%E2%80%94%20from%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20breweries%20into%20flour%2C%20a%20sustainable%20product%20that%20is%20turned%20into%20several%20goodies%20such%20as%20cookies%2C%20brownies%2C%20bread%2C%20%3Cem%3Echapatis%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20pizzas%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Eladdu%3C%2Fem%3Es.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSpent%20grain%20is%20like%20an%20invisible%20food%20in%20a%20city%20like%20Bangalore.%20You%20might%20drink%20beer%20but%20you%20would%20not%20know%20the%20value%20of%20grain%20that%20is%20being%20discarded%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%2030-year-old%20chef%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1-1697464267.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elizabeth%20upcycles%20%E2%80%98spent%20grain%E2%80%99%20into%20several%20goodies%20such%20as%20cookies%2C%20brownies%2C%20bread%2C%20chapatis%2C%20pizzas%2C%20and%20laddus.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1-1697464267.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1-1697464267-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1-1697464267-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1-1697464267-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1-1697464267-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332305%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EElizabeth%20upcycles%20%E2%80%98spent%20grain%E2%80%99%20into%20several%20goodies%20such%20as%20cookies%2C%20brownies%2C%20bread%2C%20chapatis%2C%20pizzas%2C%20and%20laddus.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTypically%2C%20if%20a%20microbrewery%20brews%20about%201%2C000%20litres%20of%20beer%20a%20day%2C%20then%20they%20will%20use%20about%20200%20kg%20of%20grains.%20Simply%20put%2C%20about%2012%2C000%20kg%20of%20byproduct%20is%20leftover%20in%20the%20process%20every%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20age-old%20relationship%20between%20brewers%20and%20bakers%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20graduate%20in%20culinary%20arts%20from%20Manipal%20Academy%20of%20Higher%20Education%2C%20Elizabeth%20has%20worked%20as%20a%20chef%20in%20numerous%20restaurants%20worldwide%20including%20Mexico%20and%20California%20for%20nearly%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20always%20been%20drawn%20to%20cooking%20naturally.%20A%20kitchen%20always%20brings%20family%20and%20friends%20together%3B%20an%20interesting%20space%20to%20be%20around.%20A%20kitchen%20is%20a%20place%20that%20can%20build%20perspectives%20on%20food%20and%20the%20supply%20chain%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CBeing%20around%20food%20has%20always%20prompted%20me%20to%20think%20of%20what%20happens%20to%20food%20before%20and%20after%20it%20is%20served%20on%20the%20plate.%20That%20curiosity%20and%20learning%20have%20shaped%20what%20my%20worth%20is%20as%20a%20cook.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20her%20fondness%20for%20cooking%20took%20her%20to%20California%20where%20she%20worked%20with%20food%20historian%20William%20Rubel%2C%20who%20has%20been%20recreating%20breads%20from%20the%2017th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20one-month-long%20internship%2C%20she%20studied%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F212039%2Fparsi-cuisine-batasa-recipe-niloufer-book-food-history-india-ana79%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehistory%20of%20bread%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20discovered%20the%20age-old%20relationship%20between%20a%20brewer%20and%20a%20baker.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1697464201.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elizabeth%20says%20that%20she%20was%20able%20to%20upcycle%201%2C200%20kg%20of%20spent%20grain%20last%20financial%20year.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1697464201.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1697464201-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1697464201-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1697464201-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSpent-grains-1697464201-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332304%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EElizabeth%20says%20that%20she%20was%20able%20to%20upcycle%201%2C200%20kg%20of%20spent%20grain%20last%20financial%20year.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EElaborating%20on%20this%20relationship%2C%20Elizabeth%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CHistorically%2C%20brewers%20and%20bakers%20used%20to%20work%20in%20similar%20spaces.%20They%20would%20share%20common%20ingredients%2C%20its%20byproducts%2C%20and%20work%20in%20a%20closed-loop%20circular%20system.%20For%20instance%2C%20bakers%20gave%20brewers%20their%20leftover%20bread%20to%20convert%20into%20beer%2C%20and%20brewers%20gave%20bakers%20leftover%20grain%20to%20make%20bread.%20Back%20then%2C%20bakers%20would%20bulk%20up%20grain%20because%20flour%20was%20an%20expensive%20commodity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThereafter%20in%202018%2C%20she%20worked%20as%20a%20food%20innovation%20research%20fellow%20at%20Future%20Food%20Institute%20Bologna%2C%20Italy.%20%E2%80%9CHere%2C%20my%20focus%20was%20on%20understanding%20a%20sustainable%20food%20system.%20As%20part%20of%20this%2C%20I%20met%20160%20stakeholders%20in%2012%20cities%20across%20the%20world%20to%20understand%20circular%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F90957%2Fsustainable-food-can-be-healthier-and-eco-friendly%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esustainable%20food%20%3C%2Fa%3Esystems%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECurious%20to%20incorporate%20the%20learnings%20into%20present-day%20work%2C%20she%20experimented%20with%20spent%20grain%20and%20upcycled%20it%20into%20products%20like%20flours%2C%20cookies%2C%20biscuits%2C%20%3Cem%3Echikki%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20granola%2C%20and%20even%20%3Cem%3Eladdus%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESpent%20grain%20into%20earthy%20loaves%2C%20laddus%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Elizabeth%20launched%20her%20startup%20%E2%80%98Saving%20Grains%E2%80%99%20to%20upcycle%20spent%20grains%20from%20breweries.%20These%20breweries%20use%20grains%20like%20barley%20and%20wheat%20in%20the%20process%20of%20brewing%20beers.%20The%20malted%20grains%20are%20soaked%20in%20hot%20water%20and%20then%20mashed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCeaMiKph9TD%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCeaMiKph9TD%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCeaMiKph9TD%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Geist%20Brewing%20Co.%20(%40drinkgeist)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20process%20is%20done%20to%20let%20starch%20and%20sugar%20leach%20out%20into%20water.%20After%20the%20sugars%20are%20extracted%2C%20the%20solids%20are%20strained%20out%20and%20what%20is%20left%20as%20a%20byproduct%20is%20known%20as%20spent%20grain.%20It%20does%20not%20have%20any%20alcohol%20content.%20And%20this%20leftover%20grain%20is%20still%20rich%20in%20protein%2C%20fibre%20and%20other%20nutrients%20that%20are%20good%20for%20consumption.%20Unfortunately%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20really%20used%20to%20its%20full%20potential%20as%20a%20food%20source%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EElizabeth%20sources%20this%20byproduct%20from%20local%20breweries.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20take%20spent%20grain%20to%20our%20facility%20where%20we%20dry%20and%20process%20it%20into%20different%20products%20like%20flours%2C%20cookies%2C%20granola%2C%20and%20biscuits.%20Technically%2C%20in%20a%20way%2C%20this%20grain%20is%20produced%20for%20free%20in%20the%20city%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20chef%20has%20collaborated%20with%20a%20bakery%20%E2%80%98Loafer%20%26amp%3B%20Co%E2%80%99%20that%20utilises%20spent%20grain%20flour%20in%20making%20their%20special%20loaf%20called%20Brewers%20Toast.%20Spent%20grain%20gives%20it%20an%20earthy%20fragrance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bakery%E2%80%99s%20founder%20Pranav%20Ullal%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20substitute%20a%20part%20of%20regular%20flours%20with%20spent%20grain%20flour%20that%20gives%20our%20breads%20a%20nice%20flavour%20when%20added%20in%20right%20amounts%20ranging%20from%205%20to%2030%20percent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCtOi8yhI0y8%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCtOi8yhI0y8%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3